						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vīra-chōḷadēva: Year 28</hi><note n="95-3">The year is given as 20 (i.e., 1202-03 A.D.) in <hi rend="italic">A.R.S.I.E.,</hi> for 1909-10.</note><hi rend="bold">= 1210-11 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged. It appears to record a gift of land in the village of Vīranārāyaṇa-chaturvēdimaṅgalam in Vīrakēraḷa-vaḷanāḍu. Mentions <hi rend="italic">Vīrakēraḷa-mannaṟai</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Vīrākēraḷa-vāykkāl</hi> as well as a land belonging to a certain Vīranārāyaṇa-brahmārāyan.</p>						

